	doi = {10.1109/WCCEST66994.2025.11389865},
	abstract = {Deepfakes are videos and images generated by AI that can convincingly imitate real individuals, posing significant threat to digital media authenticity. This paper proposes a hybrid detection model that combines ResNeXt-101 for robust spatial feature extraction with LSTM networks for capturing temporal inconsistencies across video frames. In contrast to the standalone CNN or LSTM models, the hybrid approach effectively learns both frame-level artifacts and sequential anomalies. Trained on a combination of diverse datasets like FaceForensics++, DFDC, Celeb-DF, and Kaggle DFD, the model demonstrates improved accuracy, generalization and efficiency, making it well-suited for practical deployment for low-end devices and real-time deepfake detection scenarios on desktop and cloud-based platforms.},
