	doi = {10.1109/ASSIC64892.2025.11158181},
	abstract = {This profound paper deals with the exploration of the problem of deep fakes in the context of deep learning purpose and prospects in using and detecting it. Using Deep Learning Algorithms, such as “InceptionResnetV2, VGG19 CNN, Xception, InceptionV3, EfficientNetB1, DenseNet121, Hybrid Model, LSTM, ResNext-LSTM, MRIGAN”, the study identifies the best performing algorithms applicable in the detection of deep fakes. Accuracy percentages are provided; the results are found that Xception has resulted in the highest accuracy as 99.32\%, respectively. Interestingly,”InceptionResnetV2 and DenseNet121” deliver acceptable performance since their respective accuracies are greater than 99\%. Still, some models like VGG19 and LSTM achieve lower accuracies and thus there's an optimization needed. These findings portray the upward trend toward better detection techniques as malicious deep fakes grow more prevalent, and this should fend off adverse impacts on society, such as misinformation, and infringement of privacy rights.},
