	abstract = {Deepfake videos are becoming more common and can be used to spread false information. In this paper, we present a model that can detect deepfakes by looking at both the appearance of each video frame and how the frames change over time. We use EfficientNet-B7 to extract features from each frame and Bidirectional LSTM layers to understand the sequence of frames. The model is trained on the Deepfake Detection (DFD) dataset, which has a variety of real and fake videos. Experimental results shows strong performance with training accuracy of 88\% and validation accuracy of 90 \%, indicating generalization and robustness. This approach helps in identifying even small changes or mistakes in fake videos. It can be useful for improving online safety and reducing the spread of fake content.},
